{"html_url": "http://giottojs.org/examples/simplechart", "site": {"template_engine": null, "date": "2014-12-26T22-18-28", "name": "Lux", "lux_version": "0.1.2-alpha.1", "year": 2014, "url": "http://giottojs.org", "media": "/media", "python_version": "3.4.2", "template": "partials/examples.html"}, "slug": "simplechart", "description": "A simple line and point plot of two separate series", "title": "Simple Chart", "api_url": "http://giottojs.org/ng/examples/simplechart.json", "date": "2014-12-03T00:00:00", "name": "simplechart", "image": "http://giottojs.org/examples/simplechart.png", "html": {"main": "<div id=\"page-main\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\" data-highlight>\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<h2>Simple Chart</h2>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width: 100px\" class=\"center-block\"><lux-form data-options='luxforms.typeform_jZCiS'><script>if (!this.luxforms) {this.luxforms = {};} this.luxforms.typeform_jZCiS = {\"field\": {\"showLabels\": false, \"model\": \"TypeForm\", \"type\": \"form\", \"id\": \"typeform_jZCiS\"}, \"children\": [{\"field\": {\"type\": \"fieldset\"}, \"children\": [{\"field\": {\"value\": \"svg\", \"options\": [\"svg\", \"canvas\"], \"type\": \"select\", \"name\": \"type\", \"required\": true}}]}]};</script></lux-form></div>\n\n<div data-options='gexamples.sigmoid' style='max-width: 500px' class=\"center-block\" giotto-chart></div>\n\n<p>A simple line and point plot of two separate series.</p>\n<h3>Javascript code</h3>\n<pre><code>gexamples.sigmoid = {\n    height: '80%',\n\n    data: function (chart) {\n        var X = d3.range(-5, 5, 0.5);\n\n        return [chart.xyfunction(X, function (x) {\n                    return 1/(1+Math.exp(-x));\n                }),\n                {point: chart.xyfunction(X, function (x) {\n                    var d = 1/(1+Math.exp(-x));\n                    return d*(1 - d);\n                })}\n                ];\n    },\n\n    // Callback for angular directive\n    angular: function (chart, opts) {\n\n        opts.scope.$on('formFieldChange', function (e, form, field) {\n            if (field === 'type') {\n                opts.type = form[field];\n                chart.resume();\n            }\n        });\n    }\n};\n</code></pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<script>\n\n    gexamples.sigmoid = {\n        height: '80%',\n\n        data: function (chart) {\n            var X = d3.range(-5, 5, 0.5);\n\n            return [chart.xyfunction(X, function (x) {\n                        return 1/(1+Math.exp(-x));\n                    }),\n                    {point: chart.xyfunction(X, function (x) {\n                        var d = 1/(1+Math.exp(-x));\n                        return d*(1 - d);\n                    })}\n                    ];\n        },\n\n        // Callback for angular directive\n        angular: function (chart, opts) {\n\n            opts.scope.$on('formFieldChange', function (e, form, field) {\n                if (field === 'type') {\n                    opts.type = form[field];\n                    chart.resume();\n                }\n            });\n        }\n    };\n</script>\n<div id=\"footer\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 small\">\n<p>Library released under the <a href=\"http://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause\">BSD License</a>.</p>\n<p>Copyright 2014 <a href=\"http://lucasbardella.com\">Luca Sbardella</a> and <a href=\"http://quantmind.com\">Quantmind</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}, "head": {"twitter:card": "summary_large_image", "description": "A simple line and point plot of two separate series", "title": "Simple Chart", "author": ["Luca Sbardella"]}, "modified": "2014-12-18T13:14:43", "content_type": "text/html", "author": ["Luca Sbardella"]}